<SecondaryPreamble>
<IntroductoryText>
<P>
<Text>The Secretary of State, in exercise of the powers conferred by sections 89(3)(a)<FootnoteRef Ref="f00001"/>, 89(3)(ba)<FootnoteRef Ref="f00002"/>, 105(1), 105(2)(a)<FootnoteRef Ref="f00003"/> and 105(3) of the Road Traffic Act 1988 and section 2(2) of the European Communities Act 1972<FootnoteRef Ref="f00004"/>, makes the following Regulations.</Text></P>
<P>
<Text>The Secretary of State is a Minister designated for the purpose of section 2(2) of the European Communities Act 1972 in relation to the licensing of drivers<FootnoteRef Ref="f00005"/>.</Text></P>
</IntroductoryText>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>The Secretary of State has consulted with relevant organisations as required by section 195(2)<FootnoteRef Ref="f00006"/> of the Road Traffic Act 1988.</Text></Para>
</EnactingText>
</SecondaryPreamble>
